ow pitcher of milk. The milk warmed and aerated quickly and thoroughly, producing a creamy microfoam ideal for lattes.","If you prefer a lungo, also known as a long shot, or an espresso with double the water, you have that option with this machine. You can’t adjust the water temperature, but we found that each extraction was satisfactory. Although you can allow the machine to dispense a full single or double shot, we preferred interrupting the flow just before the shot finished for a more full-bodied flavor."]},"id":"a6496b10-28c3-4da1-9270-0d4e9acee607","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Convenience"},"id":"437e0f2a-fcfd-428a-a3a8-52271c7adb8c","type":"heading"},{"data":{"path":"/eTFqNbEGsiHayWMrwp2aR.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"Once this espresso maker was set up and plugged in, we were able to start extracting shots and enjoying espresso drinks. It was simple to do, but there is an added step in maintenance – the first time you pull it out of the box, you need to prime the machine. This is also true if you let it sit for too long without water and without using it. We made sure to rinse the brew head when we were done testing and noticed a buildup of coffee grounds, so it’s a good idea give the machine a good cleaning once a week or more often, depending on how often you brew espresso. You need to empty the coffee puck bin after several shots. And you need to be sure to clean the steam wand after every use – you don’t want milk to sit in the wand for too long.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/67363-philips-saeco-intuita4.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/eTFqNbEGsiHayWMrwp2aR.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"eTFqNbEGsiHayWMrwp2aR","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/eTFqNbEGsiHayWMrwp2aR.jpg","alt":""},"id":"3444862b-1bb1-42e8-b745-fa5da4328504","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Although the water tank is a decent size, this machine uses a lot of water, so you may have